definition: to unload/to unhitch/to remove or strip/to get rid of

sentences.english: Forklift truck is very convenient equipment for loading and unloading goods.
sentences.chinese: 叉车是装卸货物时的一种非常方便的装置。

sentences.english: External conditions of packing at time of discharge. Was there any sign of having been reconditioned?
sentences.chinese: 卸货时外包装情况。有否重新整理的现象？

sentences.english: Loading and unloading inbound and outbound means of transport may be subject to supervision and control of the Customs.
sentences.chinese: 海关可以对进出境运输工具装卸货物实施监装监卸。

sentences.english: The plane was assembled in a hangar next to the airport.
sentences.chinese: 飞机在机场附近的机库里装卸货物。

sentences.english: When handling loads with cranes or trucks, caution crew members to stand clear of any overhead loads and boom.
sentences.chinese: 用吊车或卡车装卸货物时，货物和起重臂下不许站人。

sentences.english: Wed like to change the unloading port from Tokyo to Osaka.
sentences.chinese: 我们愿意把卸货港由东京改为大阪。

sentences.english: Vessel sailed from loading port to yingkou port directly . without discharging any cargo on the voyage.
sentences.chinese: 船舶由装货港直达营口港，中途未卸货。

sentences.english: Please cut off the power and unplug the reefers before discharging.
sentences.chinese: 卸货前请切断电源，拔下冷藏箱的插头。

sentences.english: The boy liked to watch the boats being loaded and unloaded.
sentences.chinese: 这男孩爱看轮船装卸货物。

sentences.english: Fax copy of Certificate of quantity and quality issued by CIQ at port of discharge.
sentences.chinese: 卸货港CIQ出具的质量数量证明传真副本。

sentences.english: The child often watches the ships being loaded and unloaded.
sentences.chinese: 那个孩子经常看船只装卸货物。

sentences.english: We need some more men to turn the ship around.
sentences.chinese: 我们需增派更多的人手使这艘船卸货返航。

sentences.english: The bill of lading must contain the name of actual port of discharge.
sentences.chinese: 提单列明具体的卸货港是有必要的。

sentences.english: The above damage caused in yingkou during discharging.
sentences.chinese: 上述残损是在营口港卸货造成的。

definition: to load sth onto a ship etc
to load or unload/to transfer/to assemble and disassemble
(of a boat) to reach the shore/to pull toward shore/close to shore/landfall
counter for the display of goods/(Tw) container (for freight transport)
to put together an order of goods
